## What Problem This Solves

Fixes an issue where operators configuring a cron job with `toolsAllow: ["web_search"]` would experience silent failure when all web search provider plugins were disabled. The job ran to completion with `status: ok` and `lastDeliveryStatus: delivered`, but the output was the model apologising that it could not search — no warning appeared in `cron_run_logs.diagnostics_summary` or `openclaw logs`.

## Why This Change Was Made

`toolsAllow` gates whether a *registered* tool is permitted; it does not validate whether the tool is *registered* at all. When all search plugins are disabled, `webSearchProviders = []` and the `web_search` tool is never added to the registry, but nothing signals this mismatch to the operator.

The fix adds a preflight check in `prepareCronRunContext` (called before the agent turn is dispatched): after runtime plugins are loaded, if the resolved `toolsAllow` contains `"web_search"` (or `"*"`) and `listWebSearchProviders()` returns an empty list, a `warn`-severity diagnostic entry is produced. This diagnostic is merged into the final run result via `mergeCronRunDiagnostics`, so it appears in `diagnostics_summary` regardless of whether the run status is `"ok"` or `"error"`.

The check is a read-only preflight with no behaviour change to the execution path; it does not block the run.

## User Impact

Operators whose cron jobs include `web_search` in `toolsAllow` but have no search provider plugin enabled will now see a warning in `diagnostics_summary`:

```
web_search tool requested (toolsAllow) but no web search provider plugin is enabled. Enable one with: openclaw plugins enable duckduckgo
```

This makes the misconfiguration visible without altering run status or blocking execution. Jobs that have a provider enabled are not affected.

## Evidence

**Modified file:** `src/cron/isolated-agent/run.ts`

Key logic added in `prepareCronRunContext` (runs after `ensureRuntimePluginsLoaded`):

```ts
const agentPayloadToolsAllow = agentPayload?.toolsAllow;
if (agentPayloadToolsAllow && agentPayloadToolsAllow.length > 0) {
  const normalizedAllow = expandToolGroups(agentPayloadToolsAllow).map((t) =>
    normalizeToolName(t),
  );
  const requestsWebSearch =
    normalizedAllow.includes("*") || normalizedAllow.includes("web_search");
  if (requestsWebSearch) {
    const webSearchProviders = listWebSearchProviders({ config: cfgWithAgentDefaults });
    if (webSearchProviders.length === 0) {
      preflightDiagnostics = normalizeCronRunDiagnostics({ /* warn entry */ });
    }
  }
}
```

The `preflightDiagnostics` field is added to `PreparedCronRunContext` and merged into the final result after `finalizeCronRun`:

```ts
const result = prepared.context.preflightDiagnostics
  ? {
      ...finalized,
      diagnostics: mergeCronRunDiagnostics(
        prepared.context.preflightDiagnostics,
        finalized.diagnostics,
      ),
    }
  : finalized;
```

TypeScript compilation (`npx tsc --noEmit`) passes with no errors introduced by this change.

